---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Abolitionist Fellowship Conference & Mission">
  <article>
    <h1>Abolitionist Fellowship Conference & Mission</h1>
    <p>
      Heritage Restored is hosting our Abolitionist Fellowship Conference on Jan 24, 2026 so we can
      have a ton of fellowship, hear from the Word, pray, and encourage one another in the work of abolition. Over half the conference time is fellowship!
     </p>
    <section>
      <h2>When &amp; Where</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Date:</strong> Saturday, January 24, 2026 | 
        <strong>Time:</strong> 11:00 AM &ndash; 3:00 PM <br />
        <strong>What:</strong>Fellowship Conference<br />
        <strong>Location:</strong> The Village Church, 3750 Sullivant Ave, Columbus, OH 43228<br />
        <strong>Cost to attend:</strong> FREE<br />
        <strong>Mission:</strong> Street evangelism at WinterJam 4-6pm. (You may be contacted by a member of Heritage Restored to confirm your participation and agreement to our rules of engagement on the street)
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Conference Schedule (11:00 AM &ndash; 3:00 PM)</h2>

      <div class="schedule-grid">
        <div class="schedule-block">
          <h3>10:30 AM &ndash; 11:00 AM</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Arrival, Setup, &amp; Check-In</strong>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="schedule-block">
          <h3>11:00 AM &ndash; 12:00 PM | Opening Session</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>11:00 | Welcome &amp; Introductions</strong><br />
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Plenary Session 1 - Logan Ramsey</strong><br />
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Plenary Session 2 - Elijah Thompson</strong><br />
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="schedule-block">
          <h3>12:00 PM &ndash; 1:00 PM | Lunch &amp; Fellowship</h3>
         </div>

        <div class="schedule-block">
          <h3>1:00 PM &ndash; 2:00 PM | Mission Preparation Session</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Plenary Session 3 - Michael Coughlin</strong><br />
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Mission Preparation &amp; Prayer</strong>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="schedule-block">
          <h3>2:00 PM &ndash; 3:00 PM | Fellowship &amp; Clean-Up</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Continued fellowship</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Venue clean-up and closing conversations</strong></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="schedule-block">
          <h3>3:00 PM Depart for Mission to WinterJam</h3>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Featured Speakers</h2>
      <div class="people-grid conference-speakers">
        <div class="person-card">
          <div class="person-photo">
            <img src="/loganramsey.jpg" alt="Pastor Logan J. Ramsey" />
          </div>
          <h2>Session 1</h2>
          <p><strong>Pastor Logan J. Ramsey</strong></p>
          <p class="person-bio">
            <strong>"The Power for Change"</strong><br />
            <strong></strong> Romans 1:16 - God's sovereign grace in salvation means that when we are
            regenerated, our lives are changed on earth. That transformation necessarily leads to faithful work,
            including abolition.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="person-card">
          <div class="person-photo">
            <img src="/elijahthompson.jpg" alt="Elijah Thompson" />
          </div>
          <h2>Session 2</h2>
          <p><strong>Elijah Thompson</strong></p>
          <p class="person-bio">
            <strong>"Tent-Making Abolitionists"</strong><br />
            <strong></strong> How to effectively work for abolition while not being able to dedicate yourself to full-time ministry.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="person-card">
          <div class="person-photo">
            <img src="/michaelcoughlin.jpg" alt="Michael Coughlin" />
          </div>
          <h2>Session 3</h2>
          <p><strong>Michael Coughlin</strong></p>
          <p class="person-bio">
            <strong>"Loving H8Rs"</strong><br />
            <strong></strong> How to respond biblically and effectively to those who oppose you. Defend the voiceless without compromising your personal holiness.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Mission at WinterJam</h2>
      <p>
        After the conference, anyone still in Columbus is invited to meet outside the Schottenstein Center for street
        ministry and conversational outreach during WinterJam. You are welcome to come only for the mission, only for
        the fellowship, or for both. We will send a short briefing as we get closer to the date.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Lightning-Testimony Invitations</h2>
      <p>
        Heritage Restored loves to hear how Christ is working through this ministry. If you have a testimony to share, let
        us know when you register&mdash;there will be a lightning-talk slot where volunteers can briefly speak about how Heritage
        Restored has impacted their walk with Christ.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Giving &amp; Support (No obligation)</h2>
      <p>
        The conference is truly free to you, but there are costs involved. if you'd like to help underwrite the costs, you can give via our <a href="/donate">donation page</a>, or feel free to offer to fund goodies or snacks when registering.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="registration">
      <h2>Register</h2>
      <p>
        This gathering is free for everyone, but we ask you to register ahead of time so we can plan food,
        seating, and any needs for the mission portion. You may be contacted by a member of Heritage Restored to confirm your participation and agreement to our rules of engagement on the street.
      </p>
      <div class="form-embed">
        <iframe
          src="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdZAGqTBUzfLCkT4mEH6M6xJKemvFSNoDvNJ1JutcH5_4Jzag/viewform?embedded=true"
          width="940"
          height="2420"
          frameborder="0"
          marginheight="0"
          marginwidth="0"
          title="Abolitionist Fellowship Conference Registration"
        >
          Loadingâ€¦
        </iframe>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Lodging</h2>
      <p>We are not offering lodging assistance at this time.</p>
    </section>
    <p class="back-to-top"><a href="#top">Back to top</a></p>
  </article>
</Layout>
